a serious claim to be paradise on earth. with world-class surfing and diving, a large number of cultural, historical and archaeological attractions, and an enormous range of accommodations, this is one of the world's most popular island destinations and one which consistently wins travel awards. bali has something to offer a very broad market of visitors from young back-packers right through to the super-rich. regions[edit] map of bali with regions colour coded south bali (kuta, bukit peninsula, canggu, denpasar, jimbaran, legian, nusa dua, sanur, seminyak, tanah lot) the most visited part of the island by far, with kuta beach and 